
print("Elijah Covert 1/17/2023 \nAt what size of a project should you start using version management software? Why? \n \nA version management software is an online management software that allows multiple people to work on a program at the same time without accidentally corrupting files and allowing them to merge their work into one when safe. When more than one person is working on a program at the same time, you should use a version management software. Any size where having a version history and other features provided by a version management software can be helpful, it is recommended to use one. Any time where you want to make sure it is safely backed up and can be recovered if you make a mistake, you should use a version management  software.")